SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Set up on the machine (or lie prone) with the pad just above your heels.
2. Press your hips down into the bench and keep your torso still.
3. Curl your heels toward your glutes through the full available range.
4. Pause and squeeze the hamstrings at the top.
5. Lower under control — never let the weight drop.
6. Breathing: Inhale at the start with the legs extended. Exhale as you curl the heels in. Inhale on the controlled return.
7. Form check: Keep the hips pressed down — lifting them off the pad cheats the hamstrings.
8. Form check: Control the negative; do not fully relax at the bottom.
9. The Bodyweight Lying Leg Curl mainly trains your Hamstrings (Biceps Femoris, Semitendinosus, Semimembranosus). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'leg_curl',
