   source_citation, rewrite_batch)
SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Set a cable high (or hold the weight) and stand side-on with feet shoulder-width.
2. Brace your core and grip the handle or weight with both hands.
3. Pull and rotate the weight down and across your body toward the opposite hip.
4. Let your hips and trunk rotate together while the arms stay fairly straight.
5. Return under control along the same path; finish all reps, then switch sides.
6. Breathing: Inhale before the chop. Exhale as you rotate and pull across. Inhale on the controlled return.
7. Form check: Rotate through the trunk and hips, not just the arms.
8. Form check: Keep the spine tall — do not crunch or round as you rotate.
9. The Diagonal Chop Cable mainly trains your Abdominals (Obliques). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'woodchop',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=woodchop] NASM EPFT 6th ed. ch.9; McGill, Low Back Disorders 2nd ed. — trunk / core training$instr$, '2085-2026-05-18'
