SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Stand tall, weights resting against the front of your thighs, palms facing you.
2. Keep a slight fixed bend in the elbows and brace your core.
3. Raise the weight straight in front of you up to shoulder height.
4. Pause briefly at the top with the arm parallel to the floor.
5. Lower slowly under control back to the thighs.
6. Breathing: Inhale before the raise. Exhale as you lift the weight. Inhale on the controlled descent.
7. Form check: Do not swing or use the torso to heave the weight up.
8. Form check: Stop at shoulder height — there is no need to go overhead.
9. The Dumbbell Single-Arm Front Raise mainly trains your Shoulders (Anterior Deltoids). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'front_raise',
