SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Stand tall holding the weight in front of your thighs with a shoulder-width grip.
2. Brace your core and keep your chest tall.
3. Pull the weight straight up along your body, leading with the elbows.
4. Stop when your elbows reach shoulder height — no higher.
5. Lower under control back to the start.
6. Breathing: Inhale before the pull. Exhale as you pull the weight up. Inhale as you lower.
7. Form check: Do not pull the elbows above shoulder height — that can pinch the shoulder.
8. Form check: Widen your grip if you feel any shoulder discomfort.
9. The Dumbbell Single-Arm Upright Row mainly trains your Shoulders (Lateral Deltoids), Upper Back (Trapezius). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'upright_row',
