SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Rest your forearms on your thighs or a bench with the wrists just past the edge, palms up.
2. Let the weight roll toward your fingertips for a full stretch.
3. Curl the weight up by flexing the wrists only.
4. Squeeze the forearms at the top of the range.
5. Lower slowly back to a full stretch.
6. Breathing: Inhale before the curl. Exhale as you curl the weight up. Inhale as you lower.
7. Form check: Move only at the wrist — the forearms stay planted.
8. Form check: Use a light load and a full range; forearms respond to control, not heavy weight.
